    <AbstractNarration>The Department of Mathematics at the University of Kansas will&lt;br/&gt;purchase advanced graphics workstations and a parallel compute&lt;br/&gt;server which will be dedicated to the support of research in the&lt;br/&gt;mathematical sciences. The equipment will be used for several&lt;br/&gt;research projects, including in particular:&lt;br/&gt;&lt;br/&gt; Parallel eigenvalue computations. (Ralph Byers)&lt;br/&gt;&lt;br/&gt; Higher dimensional immersive visualization of dynamical&lt;br/&gt; systems. (Estella Gavosto)&lt;br/&gt;&lt;br/&gt; Adaptive moving-mesh methods for numerical solution of&lt;br/&gt; evolutionary partial differential equations and its&lt;br/&gt; applications. (Wiezhang Huang)&lt;br/&gt;&lt;br/&gt; Computation in commutative algebra and algebraic geometry.&lt;br/&gt; (Craig Huneke)&lt;br/&gt;&lt;br/&gt; Spectral analysis of biological nanostructures. (Rodolfo&lt;br/&gt; Torres)</AbstractNarration>
